ass=m><span class=title> Re: cant quad -&gt; nothing worth now ?</span><hr size=1> Let's get this out of the way, I can't believe no one else has commented on this ...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And some of us have never had, wanted, or needed concussion<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I nominate this for the lamest statement of the year. The only reason I can think of the you would not need concussion is if you ONLY solo. Or maybe if you don't mind leeching exp off you friends since you can't nuke as much without it.<br>
<br>
At any rate, keep up the quadding, you won't regret it. Once you become proficient at quadding, you will always have an the option to quad if you don't want to group or you can't get a group. Like someone else mention, you will learn and develop skills that can be very useful in a group.<br>
<br>
Learning to deal with adds when you are solo will make you a better wizard. Learning how to get a situation under control when the shit hits the fan will make you a better wizard. You only have yourself to rely on so you will be forced to learn how to deal with all sorts of situations that pop up when quadding. You are not useless if you can't quad, but you will certainly be better off if you can quad. <p><div align="center" class="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial">
